instrument: "Bass"
weight: 40
---

Originally from Algonquin, Jeremy Beyer, bassist, has extensive performance
experience in a multitude of musical genres. He earned undergraduate and
graduate degrees from Northern Illinois University, BME (music education)
2006 & MM (music history) 2014.

He serves as principal bass of the Kishwaukee Symphony Orchestra in Dekalb
and was previously assistant principal bass of the Fox Valley Orchestra in
Aurora. Jeremy, along with his wife, Emily, founded the contemporary string
ensemble, New Vintage Strings, in 2018. Jeremy also performs regularly with
jazz combos and big bands throughout the suburbs.

He joined After School Special in 2014, as a member of the Fine Arts faculty
at Stevenson High School. Presently, he teaches guitar, music theory and
orchestra at Dundee-Crown High School, District 300.
